<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5879&amp;p=54474#p54474"><![CDATA[
I often use a whole byte for on/off flags on the NES, mainly for speed. I do think people underestimate how useful the 2KB of RAM in the NES can be, you can do a lot with just that amount of RAM.<br /><br />Try to make a game using only 128 bytes of RAM on the Atari 2600, now that's a challenge! =)<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=95">tokumaru</a> — Sun Dec 27, 2009 8:07 pm</p><hr />
