<title type="html"><![CDATA[Where can I store variables?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5879&amp;p=54444#p54444"><![CDATA[
Sure, the 2 KiB of internal RAM at $0000-$07FF isn't a lot, but it's surprising how much you can fit if you carefully lay out your data structures. And if you need more, you can always add 8 KiB of RAM to the cartridge, which will show up at $6000-$7FFF with  most mappers.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Sat Dec 26, 2009 9:59 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
