<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5879&amp;p=54424#p54424"><![CDATA[
<!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/CPU_memory_map">http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/CPU_memory_map</a><!-- m --><br /><br />English version:<br /><br />The NES has memory-mapped RAM available for general use from $0000 to $07FF.<br /><br />Zero page variables (e.g. STA $00) end up within $0000-00FF.<br /><br />Values pushed on the stack usually end up (depending on where you stuck the stack pointer; most people stick with page 1, e.g. $0100-01FF)) between $0100-01FF.<br /><br />Hope this helps.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3">koitsu</a> — Sat Dec 26, 2009 10:23 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
